The article discusses National Cancer Survivors Day and the celebration of millions of Americans who have battled cancer. It highlights the story of Donald Bouvet, a bladder cancer survivor, and his mission to beat cancer. The article mentions that there are nearly 16 million cancer survivors in the United States and expresses hope for a future with improved health for cancer patients. It also mentions the signing of the Federal right to try legislation, which provides expanded options for care and treatments for those facing a terminal illness. The article concludes by expressing gratitude for researchers and medical professionals who are making survivorship a reality and celebrating the enduring spirit of the American people.